The playfield is given as a rectangle where - walls are represented by entries of value Maze.WALL ('1') - the exit is represented as an entry of value Maze.EXIT ('2') - all other entries are MAZE.FREE ('0') - A playfield has exactly one exit. - The first number determines the column, the second determines the row. Row and column numbers start at 0. - Each row has the same number of columns.

Example: 6x6 maze with an exit at position (5,3) (5th row, 3rd column):
